def read_file(file_name):
    path1 = os.path.join('/datasets', file_name)
    path2 = os.path.join(file_name)
    if os.path.exists(path1):
        data = pd.read_csv(path1, sep='\t')
        return data
    elif os.path.exists(path2):
        data = pd.read_csv(path2, sep='\t')
        return data
    else:
        print('File is not found')

def floor_type (row):
    floor = row['floor'] 
    floors_total = row['floors_total'] 
    if floor == 1:
        return ''
    elif floor == floors_total:
        return ''
    else:
        return ''
data['floor_type'] = data.apply(floor_type, axis=1)

def pivot_price(column_name):
    if column_name == 'total_area':
        return data.pivot_table(index='total_area', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    if column_name == 'living_area':
        return data.pivot_table(index='living_area', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    if column_name == 'kitchen_area':
        return data.pivot_table(index='kitchen_area', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    if column_name == 'rooms':
        return data.query('rooms<10').pivot_table(index='rooms', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    if column_name == 'floor_type':
        return data.pivot_table(index='floor_type', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    if column_name == 'week_day':
        return data.pivot_table(index='week_day', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    if column_name == 'month':
        return data.pivot_table(index='month', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    if column_name == 'year':
        return data.pivot_table(index='year', values='last_price', aggfunc='median')
    return print('  ')
